eature and replace it with another qualifying spell of a level for which you have spell slots.</p>\n<h2>Spellcasting Ability</h2>\n<p>Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for your spells. You use your Wisdom whenever a spell refers to your spellcasting ability. In addition, you use your Wisdom modifier when setting the saving throw DC for a spell you cast and when making an attack roll with one.</p>\n<p><strong>Spell save DC</strong> = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier<br><strong>Spell attack modifier</strong> = your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier</p>",
